1. Reconnaissance
● Amass:Performs network mapping and subdomain enumeration.
● Subfinder: A fast subdomain enumeration tool.
● Assetfinder: Discovers related domains and subdomains.
● Shodan/Censys: Search engines for internet-connected devices.
● Aquatone: Visualizes attack surfaces and collects screenshots of target websites.
● Hakrawler: Crawls web pages to find endpoints, URLs, and JavaScript files.


2. Scanning
● Nmap:Network discovery and vulnerability scanning.
● Masscan: High-speed port scanning.
● Nikto: Scans web servers for vulnerabilities.
● OpenVAS:Acomprehensive vulnerability scanner.
● Wappalyzer: Identifies technologies and frameworks used on websites.


3. Content Discovery
● Dirsearch: Directory brute-forcing tool for web paths.
● FFUF(FuzzFaster U Fool): Flexible fuzzing tool for content discovery and fuzzing.
● Gobuster: Brute-forces URLs and DNS subdomains.
● ParamSpider: Finds URL parameters for potential exploitation.
● Waybackurls: Extracts URLs from the Wayback Machine for reconnaissance.


4. Subdomain Takeover
● Subjack: Detects subdomain takeover vulnerabilities.
● Nuclei: Customizable vulnerability scanner with templates for subdomain takeovers and
more.
● Can-I-Take-Over-X: Checks specific services for takeover possibilities.


5. Vulnerability Analysis
● BurpSuite: Comprehensive web vulnerability scanner and manual testing platform.
● OWASPZAP:Open-source web vulnerability scanner.
● sqlmap: Automated SQL injection and database takeover tool.
● XSStrike: Detects and exploits XSS vulnerabilities.
● Photon: Crawls websites to gather potential attack vectors.


6. Automation Frameworks
● Recon-ng: Reconnaissance automation framework with built-in modules.
● LazyRecon: Automates basic recon tasks.
● Osmedeus:Framework for offensive security recon and vulnerability scanning.
● BBHT(BugBountyHunting Tools): Preconfigured scripts and tools for bug hunting.
7. API Testing
● Postman: Manages and tests APIs.
● Hoppscotch: Lightweight API testing tool.
● KiteRunner: Brute-forces API endpoints.


8. Exploitation
● Metasploit Framework: Comprehensive exploitation platform.
● Commix:Exploits command injection vulnerabilities.
● XXEInjection Payloads: Automates XXE vulnerability testing.
● PayloadsAllTheThings: A repository for testing various vulnerabilities.


9. Reporting & Workflow
● ReconNote: Organizes recon findings.
● SecurityTrails: Collects data on domains, DNS records, and more.
● HackMD/Obsidian: For documentation and note-taking.
● Vulners: Search engine for vulnerability details and exploit information.


10. Other Handy Tools
● CyberChef: Processes and decodes data.
● DNSDumpster: Investigates DNS servers and their records.
● Certspotter: Finds SSL certificates for a domain.
● Httprobe: Probes URLs for HTTP/HTTPS endpoints.
● Dnsx:Fast and customizable DNS resolution tool.


11. All-in-One Tools
● Naabu:Fast port scanning tool.
● BugcrowdNinja Tools: A collection of bug bounty tools pre-configured for ease of use.
● TheHarvester: Gathers emails, subdomains, and other metadata.
